title: China could target French wine if Paris pushes for EU tariffs
summary: BEIJING, Feb 11 () - China could launch investigations into French wines or impose "reciprocal tariffs" on EU products if the French government ‌pushes for tariffs on Chinese goods, a social media account affiliated ‌with Chinese broadcaster CCTV said on Wednesday. A French government strategy report published on Monday urged ​the EU to consider an unprecedented 30% across-the-board tariff on Chinese goods or a 30% depreciation of the euro against the renminbi to counter a surge of cheap imports
